    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Truer Test</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Don Stephens letter discusses Atlanta Braves relief pitcher John Rocker's comments in Sports Illustrated (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I don't understand what the big deal is about John Rocker riding the subway in New York.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I don't understand what the big deal is about John Rocker riding the subway in New York.</p>
        <p>If he really wanted to prove himself, he would walk through Central Park wearing a halter and shorts.</p>
        <p>DON STEPHENS  Memphis</p>
      </block>
